A pupil at the Winnie Mandela Secondary School has her temperature measured as she enters the school premises. JOHANNESBURG - The revised school calendar is out. This is the second time this year that the calendar has been revised due to the impact of COVID-19. Public schools will resume classes on 24 August. READ: Cosas threaten to shut down private schools There will be a week's break from 26 to 30 October. The school year will end on 15 December for Grades R to 11. The 2020 matric examinations will be completed on the 15 December. READ: Pupils want to finish school year Marking will conclude on 22 January 2021 and results will be released on 23 February. Teachers will begin the 2021 school year on 25 January and pupils a few days later. The Basic Education Minister will issue directions for the sector next week. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.